<HEADLINE>
TEXAS' RICKY WILLIAMS ASKS TO HONOR DOAK WALKER
</HEADLINE>
 12 NOTES-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JIMMY BURCH 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Texas tailback Ricky Williams, winner of the 1997 Doak Walker
National Running Back Award, has made a special request to NCAA
officials to wear jersey No. 37 in Saturday's game against Oklahoma
as a tribute to the former SMU star who died Sept. 27.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, a senior who became close to the Walker family after
winning the award, seeks a one-game exception to wear Walker's
number in his final appearance at the Cotton Bowl, the stadium
dubbed ``the house that Doak built'' because it was twice expanded
to meet growing ticket demands during Walker's career at SMU.
</P>
<P>
   John Bianco, Texas' associate director of media relations, said
Sunday that school officials had not received word from the NCAA on
Williams' request. Williams wore a helmet decal with No. 37 on it
to honor Walker while rushing for a career-high 350 yards and five
touchdowns during a 54-33 victory against Iowa State.
</P>
<P>
   By doing so, Williams became the first back in NCAA history to
top the 300-yard mark in consecutive games. Williams rushed for 318
yards and six touchdowns in a 59-21 rout of Rice on Sept. 26. ABC
PICKS A&AMP;M GAME
</P>
<P>
   ABC has selected Nebraska-Texas A&AMP;M as Saturday's 2:30 p.m.
telecast (WFAA/Channel 8), network officials announced Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The decision finalized starting times for this week's Big 12
games, which will include two 6 p.m. telecasts on other networks:
Oklahoma State-Texas Tech (Fox Sports Southwest) and Kansas
State-Colorado (FX). The Texas-Oklahoma game will be shown at 11:30
a.m. on KXTX/Channel 39. TECH INJURIES MOUNT
</P>
<P>
   Texas Tech coach Spike Dykes said starting offensive linemen
Curtis Lowery (sprained knee) and Steve McFadden (sprained ankle)
are among six players expected to miss Saturday's home game against
Oklahoma State.
</P>
<P>
   Dykes said both linemen are out, along with reserve defensive
end Devin Lemons (sprained knee). Listed as doubtful are linebacker
Ty Ardoin (chest bruise), cornerback Antwan Alexander (chest
bruise) and receiver Tim Baker (knee).
</P>
<P>
   ``Our training room looks like a MASH unit,'' Dykes said. ``We
need Oral Roberts over here for a couple of days to lay on some
hands.'' Big 12 honors three
</P>
<P>
   Three players with Texas connections were selected as the Big 12
players of the week: Williams (offensive), Texas A&AMP;M linebacker Dat
Nguyen (defense) and Nebraska punt returner Joe Walker (special
teams).
</P>
<P>
   Williams rushed for 350 yards and five touchdowns against Iowa
State, Nguyen had eight tackles and two turnovers in a 24-21
victory against Kansas, and Walker, a Lamar High School graduate,
returned a punt 73 yards for the game-winning touchdown in a 24-17
victory against Oklahoma State.
RECORD-SETTING NIGHT
</P>
<P>
   Texas set or tied 15 NCAA records in a 54-33 victory against
Iowa State, including seven by tailback Ricky Williams. The list:
</P>
<P>
   Career rushing TDs: Williams, 65 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Career total TDs: Williams, 67 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Career points by non-kicker: Williams, 404 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Consecutive 300-yard rushing games: Williams, 2 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Rushing yards in consecutive games: Williams, 668 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Fastest to 1,000 rushing yards (season): Williams, 5 games (ties
record)
</P>
<P>
   Rushing TDs in consecutive games: Williams, 11 (ties record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra points scored (game): Tony Holmes, 2 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra points scored (season): Holmes, 2 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra point attempts (game): Holmes, 2 (ties record)
</P>
<P>
   Longest defensive extra point return: Holmes, 100 yards (ties
record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra points scored by team (game): Texas, 2 (record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra points attempts by team (game): Texas, 2 (ties
record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra points scored by team (season): Texas, 2 (ties
record)
</P>
<P>
   Defensive extra point attempts by team (season): Texas, 2 (ties
record)
</P>
</TEXT>
