<SLUG> BC-FBC-ASU-FOLLOW-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SNYDER INSISTS SUN DEVILS CAN TURN SEASON AROUND  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   It is the anti-Devil.
</P>
<P>
   The 1998 Arizona State football team has emerged as a strange
alter-ego to the 1996 Sun Devils who went to the Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   That group found unlikely ways to win. This season's team finds
unlikely ways to lose. Bounces and breaks often went the 1996
team's way. This group wouldn't recognize good fortune if it bit it
in the shoulder pad.
</P>
<P>
   It has meant the difference between a 5-0 and 2-3 start.
</P>
<P>
   ``I cannot go in front of my team now and say you played like
dogs. Because they didn't,'' ASU Coach Bruce Snyder said.
</P>
<P>
   Snyder spent most of Sunday trying to get a handle on his team
after a devastating 35-24 loss Saturday to Southern California. The
Trojans outscored the Sun Devils, 22-0, in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   He also awaits word on starting quarterback Ryan Kealy, who was
knocked out of the game in the first series because of a
concussion. Snyder had nothing new to report but is optimistic that
Kealy will return to practice Tuesday, and he is expected to start
Saturday against Notre Dame.
</P>
<P>
   Kealy's absence against USC was only part of the story. Two
fourth-quarter plays did irreparable damage: a blocked punt and an
interception. Both were returned for touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   Add a botched defensive play against Washington and ASU could be
3-0, instead of 1-2, in the Pac-10.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we should actually have a lot of confidence right now
because we know if we ever straighten up, we're going to be good,''
Snyder said. ``Maybe we don't understand how to win yet. But I have
a totally different taste in my mouth right now than I did after
the BYU (loss).''
</P>
<P>
   But Snyder also knows good teams find ways to win, and he's
still searching for an answer as to why this team can't close the
deal. Chemistry and immaturity are candidates.
</P>
<P>
   The clock always seems to run out on the Sun Devils, and the
season is beginning to tick away. ASU needs answers, and fast.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils sit in seventh place in the conference. They must
begin winning league games if they want a shot at a decent bowl.
Their Rose Bowl hopes are all but dead. Next in line for Pac-10
teams are, in descending order, the Holiday Bowl in San Diego, the
Sun Bowl in El Paso and the Aloha and Mele Kalikimaka bowls in
Honolulu.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think if we can get our team emotionally and physically
prepared like they were (Saturday) for the next six games, we'll
win a lot of those games,'' Snyder said. ``Six in a row would be
huge.''
</P>
<P>
   That would make ASU 8-3, the same regular season record the Sun
Devils had in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Six in a row won't be easy. Notre Dame visits Saturday, and ASU
has games remaining against undefeated Arizona and Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   Snyder has only the Fighting Irish on his mind now, and if his
team hopes to win, it needs to prevent the mistakes that cost the
team against USC: a punt team breakdown that allowed USC's Antuan
Simmons to go untouched as he got a hand on Stephen Baker's punt,
and an offensive breakdown on the interception return.
</P>
<P>
   ``One, you go back and look at the punt,'' Snyder said. ``You
coach the technique of it, or you change the personnel. Two, with
the interception for a touchdown, I think partially that could be
attributed to a young quarterback trying to make a play who has
very little playing time and wasn't emotionally prepared.''
</P>
<P>
   Chad Elliott replaced Kealy during the first series. Elliott had
a solid game, despite some rookie mistakes, but he threw an
interception with 8:27 remaining in the game that David Gibson
returned for a touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   ``We went to their place and outhit them,'' Snyder said. ``The
tempo was ours. I'm not mad at my team from that standpoint. I'm
mad at the other stuff.
</P>
<P>
   ``We couldn't close the game.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-05-98 0528EDT &QL; 
