<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-KICKERS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DAVIS LIKES BEATING TEAM THAT DUMPED HIM 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - Greg Davis, shipped out by the Cardinals two
seasons ago, wasn't mad Sunday, but he certainly got his ``evens.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I have to admit this feels pretty good,'' said Davis, who
kicked field goals of 51, 40 and 34 yards for the Raiders on Sunday
as Oakland extinguished his former team, 23-20. ``I didn't want to
build this up too much, but when the fourth quarter rolled around,
I really wanted this one bad.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was really bitter when they waived me _ it took the rest of
the season to get over it. But in retrospect, they made the right
decision. At that point, I was really upset with the organization
and had a terrible attitude. That's not healthy in the locker
room.''
</P>
<P>
   The parting stemmed from an two-year contract dispute. Davis
claimed the Cardinals owed him bonus money that they refused to
pay. The arbitrator ruled for him.
</P>
<P>
   ``Once that came down, I knew I was gone,'' Davis said. ``But it
was really hard to come to work for two years while it was going
on.''
</P>
<P>
   Ironically, while Davis made good from 51 yards into the wind,
Cards Coach Vince Tobin elected not to allow his kicker, Joe
Nedney, to attempt a 52-yarder with the wind in third quarter, and
a 55-yarder into the wind that could've been a game-tying kick on
the game's final play.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had a pulled groin. What was their excuse?'' said Davis,
whose injury resulted in his being pulled from kickoff duties by
halftime.
</P>
<P>
   Actually, however, the injury helped him on field goals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm wearing a strap that restricts my leg, but on a shorter
distance kick, I'm able to swing it. It makes me use the motion I
need to kick. I can't over swing or I'll snap my leg. It's weird,
it's almost like the injury helped me. I hit from 52 in pre-game,
so I knew I could make it if I was asked.''
</P>
<P>
   Like many in Sun Devil Stadium, Davis said he didn't understand
why Tobin declined to give Nedney an opportunity to tie the score.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a good kicker,'' he said. ``He has a real strong leg.
From where he was, it was a 40 percent kick, which is a heck of a
lot better percentage than any other play they could've run. You
can't risk running a play with five seconds left.''
</P>
<P>
   Nedney, who made field goals of 41 and 29 yards, said he would
have enjoyed the game-tying chance but said it was a coaching
decision.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was one of those situations, I had 56 yards with a little
breeze in my face, and they thought they could hit a quick out and
get me a couple more yards,'' he said. ``He was trying to help me.
I can't say I would've made it, but I'd have given it a good ride.
I live for those chances.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
