<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE TUESDAY COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, Oct. 6, 1998, are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ PARIS _ I'm always happy to arrive in Paris. I'd
have been even happier if my luggage had arrived, too. (Murray, Cox
News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ When I was 7, I trusted my
country. I trusted my president. It may have been the last of an
era. My 31-year-old son never had it so good. We were talking this
morning over breakfast, about the mess in Washington. I listened
and learned. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ Forget therapy and self-help books. People would
lead better, happier, more responsible lives if they put their
stuff in boxes more often. Simple, I know. But it cannot be denied.
(Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
