<P>
   TEEN-FAME (Newcastle, Wash.) As a little girl _ not long ago _
Vicki Noon used to clown around for home videos, pretending to be
Ariel of ``The Little Mermaid.'' Like Ariel on her seaside rock,
Vicki would climb atop her bunk bed and sing achingly in her
bright, powerful voice about being ``part of your world.'' Vicki is
13 now, and if she became part of our world any faster, she'd risk
getting the bends. After just a year or so of voice lessons, the
Newcastle eighth-grader has already landed three plum roles,
including the juvenile lead in Seattle's A Contemporary Theatre's
fall production of ``Violet.'' PHOTO.
</P>
