<HEADLINE>
`LOST IN SPACE' A LOSER; `PERFECT MURDER' IMPERFECT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``Lost in Space''  &LR; _ The feature-length rehash of
the '60s TV show is little more than a rip-off of ``Swiss Family
Robinson'' in spacesuits. Nothing new here.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``A Perfect Murder''  &LR; _ The retelling of Alfred Hitchcock's
``Dial M for Murder'' isn't bad for a while, but the filmmakers
miss a crucial plot point involving a key. The original Ray
Milland-Grace Kelly thriller, in spite of its obvious bow to 3-D
technology, was directed by the unquestioned master of the form. If
you don't believe me, rent both. It makes for an enlightening
double feature.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Mrs. Dalloway'' &LR;  _ Vanessa Redgrave, without doubt one of the
finest actresses of her generation, tries desperately to breathe
life into this moribund costume drama about an older woman reunited
with a lover she left decades earlier.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Con''  &LR; _ Rebecca DeMornay stars as a woman for whom money
can't buy happiness in this lukewarm comedy.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Artists Rights Foundation has filed a protest against a Utah
home-video retailer for excising the brief nude scene between
Leonardo DiCaprio and Kate Winslet in the megahit, ``Titanic,''
according to the latest issue of Video Store magazine. Don
Biesinger of Sunrise Family Video in American Fork, Utah, has been
editing the scene ``for customers looking for a G-rated version of
the movie.'' He charges $5 more for the edited edition.
</P>
<P>
   ``Art is what it is,'' Foundation director Kathy Garmezy wrote.
``For better or worse. And a decent respect for the talent of
artists demands that the public be allowed to judge its worth for
themselves, without referees.'' Paramount, the film's distributor,
said that ``any unauthorized alteration of its film violates its
rights under copyright, trademark, and other laws.''
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; Oct. 13: &LR;  ``The X Files,'' ``The Lost
World,'' ``The Big One,'' ``Black Dog,'' ``Major League: Back to
the Minors,'' ``Never 2 Big,'' ``It's a Gift,'' ``Million Dollar
Legs,'' ``You Can't Cheat an Honest Man,'' ``Dancer, Texas,''
``Payback,'' ``Into Thin Air: Death on Everest,'' ``You're Telling
Me,'' ``Year of the Horse,'' ``The Ripper,'' ``Tarzan and the Lost
City,'' ``I Got the Hook Up.''  &UR; Oct. 20 &LR; : ``Deep Impact,'' ``His
Bodyguard,'' ``Species 2,'' ``Chitty Chitty Bang Bang,'' ``Red
Corner,'' ``The Odd Couple II,'' ``Picnic at Hanging Rock,'' ``Hope
Floats.''  &UR; Oct. 27:  &LR; ``Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas,'' ``The
Butcher Boy,'' ``Cats,'' ``The Lion King II: Simba's Pride,''
``Operation Delta Force 2.'' Nov. 3: ``Godzilla.'' Nov. 10: ``The
Horse Whisperer,'' ``Artemisia,'' ``Music from Another Room.''
</P>
</TEXT>
