   IMPEACHMENT-CLINTON (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee
deliberates on whether to launch an investigation of President
Clinton's role in the White House sex scandal and its aftermath.
Chairman Henry Hyde, R-Ill., tells members they don't have to judge
Clinton's conduct at this point but urges them instead ``to decide
whether to look further or look away.'' By DAN FREEDMAN.
