Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-NL-NOTEBOOK _ ATLANTA _ Inside the Braves' clubhouse.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-INDIANS-YANKEES _ Advancing ALCS. (Rosenberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-SPENCER _ New York's Shane Spencer has the baseball nation
scratching its head. After being called up from Columbus in
September, he has turned into a one-man wrecking crew. The
26-year-old rookie had two homers and four of the Yankees' nine
RBIs in the division series. And he's being compared to the
character from ``The Natural.'' (Rosenberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-AL-NOTEBOOK _ ALCS notes. (Rosenberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATECH-NCSTATE _ After dominating performances against
Florida State and Syracuse, Torry Holt of N.C. State has emerged as
one of the nation's top receivers. Holt is currently second in the
nation in receiving yards per game and figures to present problems
for the Georgia Tech secondary in Saturday's ACC contest in
Raleigh, N.C. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UGA-TENN _ Florida and Tennessee have been the dominant
teams in the SEC East for many years, but now it appears that
Georgia is rapidly closing the gap. Georgia ended its long losing
streak to Florida last season and finished second to the Vols in
the division. Saturday, the Bulldogs have a chance to end a
seven-game drought against Tennessee and move into sole possession
of first place in the East. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-LONGHORNS-DEFENSE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ It may be small. It may
be fleeting. But it is progress, and what the Texas Longhorns'
defense did in a 59-21 win over Rice last weekend put a contented
feeling in its coach's heart, which is progress of a whole
different kind. (Wangrin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
