<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-05 15:11 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0054 &Cx1f; taf-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUD     10-05 0241
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories in sight at this hour from The
N.Y. Times News Service for Tuesday, Oct. 6.
</P>
<P>
   COYNE-SCULPTURE (New York) _ Petah Coyne, a sculptor who scorns
stone and metal in favor of horsehair. By Judith Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
