   The museum is closed on Monday. A service charge of $2.75 is
added to each ticket purchased by telephone, at (215) 235-7469.
Tickets can also be purchased at the museum.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A Cathay Pacific Deal For Fall Travel to Asia &LR;
</P>
<P>
   With Asian economies struggling, Cathay Pacific is offering a
break on a single-rate pass for travel to Hong Kong and 17 other
cities in Asia. The All Asia Pass includes a round-trip economy
seat from either Los Angeles or New York to Hong Kong and a month
of unlimited economy-class travel to the other cities in Asia. The
standard rate is $999, but adults over 55, full-time students under
27 and anyone who has registered on the airline's Web site will pay
$100 less.
</P>
<P>
   The pass is valid for travel through Dec. 15 on itineraries
chosen at the time of purchase. Tickets must be bought 30 days
before departure, but for $100 you can buy them as little as five
days ahead. All American taxes and fees are included, but most
airport taxes outside the United States are not. Frequent-flier
mileage cannot be earned on the pass.
</P>
<P>
   Travel is available from Hong Kong to these cities: Jakarta,
Denpasar (Bali) and Surabaya in Indonesia; Tokyo, Fukuoka, Nagoya,
Osaka and Sapporo in Japan; Kuala Lumpur and Penang in Malaysia;
Manila and Cebu in the Philippines; Singapore; Seoul, South Korea;
Colombo, Sri Lanka; Taipei, Taiwan; and Bangkok, Thailand. These
cities were available last year, but this year Cathay Pacific has
added some options. Now destinations in Australia, China, New
Zealand, India, South Africa, Vietnam, Thailand and Turkey may be
included for $200 to $500 extra. The pass may be extended from the
basic 30-day period to 45 days for an additional $100. Upgrades to
first or business class on the trans-Pacific flight are also
available.
</P>
<P>
   Cathay Pacific offers two nonstop flights a day to Hong Kong
from Los Angeles, and daily direct service from New York, through
Vancouver. More information is available at (800) 228-4297 or
www.cathay-usa.com/.
</P>
