<P>
   &UR; IS THIS DIRTY? &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Dean of Women at an exclusive girls' school was lecturing
her students on sexual morality. `We live today in very difficult
times for young people. In moments of temptation,` she said, `ask
yourself just one question: Is an hour of pleasure worth a lifetime
of shame?`
</P>
<P>
   A young woman rose in the back of the room and said, `Excuse me,
but how do you make it last an hour?`
</P>
<P>
   &UR; KIDS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Johnny watched, fascinated, as his mother smoothed cold cream on
her face.
</P>
<P>
   `Why do you do that, mommy?` he asked.
</P>
<P>
   `To make myself beautiful,` said his mother, who then began
removing the cream with a tissue.
</P>
<P>
   `What's the matter?` asked Little Johnny. `Giving up?`
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``You get the feeling that if Ross Perot hadn't gotten rich,
he'd be writing manifestos in a cabin up there in Montana?''
</P>
<P>
   ``If you are a basketball fan, the NBA season is in real danger
this year because of this player lockout thing. But the good news:
Looks like Shawn Kemp may have enough illegitimate kids to start a
rival league.''
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton could earn as much as $10 million if he would
write a book. How could he write a book? You saw his testimony. He
can't remember anything that happened! 'I may have been
President.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``More problems for President Clinton. Now he's being sued by
David Copperfield. He said he came up with the idea of the
disappearing cigar trick.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Clinton seems to be rebounding. You hear his new philosophy?
'No Stain, No Gain.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``The tabloids are reporting that Monica Lewinsky may be dating
a doctor. Her last boyfriend was Clinton, now she's dating a
doctor. I guess she's got a thing for men who play golf and ask
strangers to take their clothes off.''
</P>
<P>
   ``People who want to see Dan Quayle elected President have
opened their own Web site. If you want to find them, they're at
www.no-chance-in-hell.com.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``At a recent event, Michael Bolton defended President Clinton
saying, 'To be human is to be flawed.' He went on to say, 'And I
know what I'm talking about because I am Michael Bolton.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``This year, for the fifth time in a row, Bill Gates topped
Forbes Magazine's list of the richest people in America. To give
you an idea of how rich Gates is, the second guy on the list was
the guy who cleans Gates' pool.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A toy company announced that it's coming out with a brand-new
virtual pet that talks, eats, burps and passes gas. Apparently, it
was designed to show young women what it's like to be married.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday, Gillette announced their going to lay off 10
percent of their work force. Although now it may not happen,
because as soon as they announced the layoffs, sales of razor
blades went way up.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It was reported today that Linda Tripp has passed a lie
detector test where she has denied tampering with the Monica
Lewinsky tapes. Afterwards, Tripp said, 'Tampering with secretly
recorded conversations between friends would be wrong.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``This week Hillary Clinton attended the eighth annual
conference for the wives of heads of states. Apparently, it's
payback time, because this year's conference was held at Hedonism
II.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Sharon Stone said that recent media speculation about whether
she's pregnant is an invasion of the most private part of her body.
Stone said that part of her body is reserved for her husband, her
gynecologist and the people who see her movies.''
</P>
