<HEADLINE>
(HLW)
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the stories that New York Times editors are planning
for the Page 1 of Tuesday, Oct. 6. The N.Y. Times News Service
supervisor is Henry Louis Warnken. The final FRONTPAGE will move
later in the evening.
</P>
<P>
   For copy info: (888) 346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   For graphics, map, photo info: (888) 603-1036.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACH (Washington) _ Ledeall on developments in the
House Judiciary Committee as it considers whether to conduct
impeachment hearings. By Alison Mitchell and Lizette Alvarez.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SCENE (Washington) _ The atmosphere at the impeachment
hearings. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   NY-MEDICAID (New York) _ New York City will soon require all its
Medicaid recipients to enter managed care. The preparations for
this major shift, unsurprisingly, have been troubled. By Jennifer
Steinhauer.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-U.N. (United Nations) _ In a tough report that was
welcomed by the United States, Secretary General Kofi Annan said
today that using a campaign of ``terror and violence,'' Serbian
security forces are continuing to carry out punitive operations
against ethnic Albanians in Kosovo province. By Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-ECON (Washington) _ Ledeall: President Clinton is
scheduled to make an unusual appearance this evening before the
finance ministers of 22 nations, including the seven largest
industrial countries and most of the major emerging market
countries hit by the global turmoil. Clinton's speech comes at a
moment of deep anxiety at the annual meetings of the World Bank and
the IMF, which in turn is reflected in the market. By David E.
Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   COLUMBIA-HEALTHCARE-SUIT (Undated) _ After years of
investigating allegations of fraud at the Columbia/HCA Healthcare
Corp., the government announced yesterday that it has sued the
health care giant for engaging over more than a decade in a scheme
to cheat federal health programs such as Medicare out of
potentially billions of dollars. By Kurt Eichenwald.
</P>
</TEXT>
