 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dylan album now available on CD after long vinyl relerase
 &HT;    By Russ Devault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The title's misleading and a bit cumbersome _ ``The Bootleg
Series Vol. 4: Bob Dylan _ Live 1966 The 'Royal' Albert Hall'
Concert'' _ but the significance of the 15 songs justifies its
release. The music, actually performed at the Free Trade Hall in
Manchester, England, has been available on vinyl and duplicate
tapes, but never on CD. It showcases Dylan at the peak of his
creative powers and cultural influence. Columbia will release the
two-CD set Oct. 13.
</P>
<P>
   -- dc Talk, ``Supernatural'' (Virgin). Highest-ever
``Christian'' act debut hits Billboard at No. 4. Grade: C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Jay-Z, ``Vol. 2. . .Hard Knock Life'' (Roc-A-Fella/Def Jam).
Grade: B+.
</P>
<P>
   -- John Mellencamp, ``John Mellencamp'' (Columbia). Fresh start
on new label for veteran rocker. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- Joni Mitchell, ``Taming the Tiger'' (Reprise). Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- Outkast, ``Aquemini'' (LaFace). Atlanta duo retains
geographic roots. Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Practical Magic'' soundtrack (Reprise). Features two Stevie
Nicks cuts produced by Sheryl Crow.
</P>
<P>
   -- Travis Tritt, ``No More Looking Over My Shoulder'' (Warner
Bros.) Cathartic set of songs from Paulding County hitmaker. Due
Oct. 13.
</P>
