32-year-old Christina Marie White, is ``not considered a suspect,''
says sheriff's spokesperson Michael Irving, but investigators want
to talk to her. The dead man's name has not been released. By Lisa
Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   HMO-PHARMACEUTICAL (Los Angeles) _ California Sen. Herschel
Rosenthal has called on the state Department of Corporation to
investigate a controversial proposal in which a New York
pharmaceutical firm would pay managed care giant Foundation Health
Systems $1 million a month for showing preference to its drugs.
Rosenthal chairs the Senate Insurance Committee.
</P>
<P>
   By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOSTON-CHIX-BANKRUPTCY (Los Angeles) _ Boston Chicken files for
Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection and closes 178 of its restaurants
as part of a restructuring plan. No stores in Southern California
will be closed, however. By Greg Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   PAMC-RESTRUCTURE (Los Angeles) _ Fremont General Corp. has
restructured its merger offer for Woodland Hills-based
PacificAmerica Money Center Inc., pegging the value of the deal on
performance targets PacificAmerica must meet. Shareholders were
pessimistic, cutting the value of PacificAmerica in half on early
trading Monday. By Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN _ Let the hire beware. Daily News columnist Ken
Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational behavior, answers
readers' questions on workplace ethics and relationships.
</P>
