<P>
   BOEING-DELIVERIES (Seattle) Boeing delivered only 123 airplanes
in the third quarter, far less than the 140 plans it expected.
Analysts say this does not bode well for Boeing's 4th quarter
numbers. Boeing is under great pressure to turn a profit. Problems
in Asia are mostly to blame. Boeing said it still believes it can
meet its total 1998 deliveries by re-selling airplanes intended for
Asia but which are now in storage.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Seattle) Tuesday was the day the Sonics were
supposed to open training camp, but that obviously won't happen.
The NBA canceled the remaining 114 exhibition games that hadn't
already been scrubbed, and NBA commissioner David Stern told the
Rocky Mountain News that the season won't start on time and
shouldn't even be played if more than one-fourth of the games are
canceled. Talking to Sonics president Wally Walker, coach Paul
Westphal and assistant coach Dwane Casey for the team's outlook.
</P>
