   WORLD-ECON (Washington) _ Ledeall: President Clinton is
scheduled to make an unusual appearance this evening before the
finance ministers of 22 nations, including the seven largest
industrial countries and most of the major emerging market
countries hit by the global turmoil. Clinton's speech comes at a
moment of deep anxiety at the annual meetings of the World Bank and
the IMF, which in turn is reflected in the market. By David E.
Sanger.
</P>
