</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PHOTO-FULL-UPDATE-NYT </SLUG>
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 10/05/98. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) WASHINGTON -- Oct. 05, 1998 -- CLINTON-IMPEACH, 10-05 --
House Judiciary Chairman Henry Hyde conferring with Rep. Robert
Barr during the hearing addressing whether Congress should open a
formal impeachment investigation against President Clinton. ``We
are not here to pass judgment on anyone,'' says Hyde, opening the
committee session. ``We are here to ask and answer this one single
question - based on what we now know, do we have a duty to look
further, or to look away?'' (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
