<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-05 21:50 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0899 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FASHION-SIDEBAR07-COX     10-05 0391
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FASHION-SIDEBAR07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eleanor Lambert's tips on timeless style
 &HT;    Sidebar to FASHION-LAMBERT
 &HT;    By Cara Anna
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Keep two pairs of shoulder pads handy, one broad and the other
very slight. Shoulders go from natural to medium or wide from
season to season, and a well-fitting tailored suit can be updated
accordingly.
</P>
<P>
   _ A good wool jersey day dress, loose enough to be belted but
smart alone, and with pockets, will take you anywhere for years.
</P>
<P>
   _ Never discard a comfortable pair of gold or black satin
evening shoes. One or the other will go with anything.
</P>
<P>
   _ There are timeless period styles that come back ``in fashion''
every few years and are worth investing in for important occasions.
A beautiful example is a draped ``Greek goddess'' evening gown or a
Victorian ballgown. A Russian cossack coat, a fur toque, a Chinese
mandarin coat or an antique Spanish shawl are blue-chip acquisition
possessions.
</P>
<P>
   _ It is a wise idea to keep a bright red dress in your closet.
You never know when it will be the only right thing to wear.
</P>
<P>
   _ Military styles like the middy dress, trench coat, the anorak,
or anything with epaulettes and brass buttons always look snappy
and timeless.
</P>
<P>
   _ You may not be a ``hat person,'' but you'll always need a
pretty hat or turban occasionally. Nothing is so depressing as a
frantic last-minute scramble for required head covering.
</P>
<P>
   _ Most people today have a drawer full of kid gloves they never
wear, but the day will come. Good gloves, like an alligator
handbag, should never be discarded. That goes for fine leather
belts, Hermes scarves, beaded evening bags and heirloom fur coats.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't underestimate the possibilities of a vintage Paris
original by Balenciaga, Hubert de Givenchy, Marc Bohan of Dior,
Yves St. Laurent, Pierre Cardin, etc. They turn up at auctions
often nowadays and often sell much below their original cost.
Anyway, your granddaughter will probably be wearing it a generation
hence.
</P>
<P>
   _ Timeless essentials: one black dinner dress with graceful body
lines; one jazzy cocktail dress, preferably black; and one dinner
suit with long or short skirt or pants. A blouse is optional these
days.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
