<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOSTELS-SOUTH07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Not all hostels are created equal; ask right questions before
you go
 &HT;    By By Cara Anna
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Hostels are cheap, usually less than $20 a night, and for that
you have to put up with a little something.
</P>
<P>
   In St. Augustine, for example, there's just one bathroom. That
means one toilet, one shower. Bring your own soap.
</P>
<P>
   Savannah's hostel could be cleaner.
</P>
<P>
   And the Key West hostel sleeps eight to 10 people in a room in
bunk beds. That's normal.
</P>
<P>
   Florida and coastal Georgia have several hostels within a day's
drive _ Clearwater Beach, Fort Lauderdale, Daytona Beach and
Florida City, for starters. Each requires a little research.
</P>
<P>
   Are hostels noisy? Do they have storage space for valuables? Are
there curfews? Each place is different. Call _ they've heard the
questions before.
</P>
<P>
   Here is our tip sheet on four places within a half-day's drive.
</P>
<P>
   Savannah
</P>
<P>
   Location: On the edge of the historic district. A supermarket is
on the next block, and everything is within walking distance (if
you don't mind walking a mile or two).
</P>
<P>
   Price: $15 (As with other hostels, you may have to pay a linen
deposit of around $2.)
</P>
<P>
   Reservations: Not necessary.
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (912) 236-7744
</P>
<P>
   Ambience: Nice. The owner often hangs out in the living room
upstairs and chats. If you like his dog, he might let you walk it.
If you're really energetic, you can help with renovations on the
Victorian house.
</P>
<P>
   Note: The owner closes for a couple of months each year to do
his own traveling.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando/Kissimmee
</P>
<P>
   Location: Five miles from Disney World, in a converted motel. A
convenience store/pharmacy is across the street.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $19 (A $5 key deposit _ refundable _ is required.)
</P>
<P>
   Reservations: Recommended.
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (407) 396-8282
</P>
<P>
   Ambiance: Stocked. A pool and a lake with paddleboats out back,
along with a volleyball area and barbecue. Kitchen, laundry, TV
room and padlock rentals for storage. The bottom rack in the fridge
is marked ``free food'' (if you don't label your stuff, everyone
gets it). A shuttle to the nearby attractions is available at $7.75
per round trip.
</P>
<P>
   St. Augustine
</P>
<P>
   Location: In the middle of the (extremely touristy) historic
district. Everything but the beach is within walking distance. Not
a lot of night life outside the bars and the $3 movie.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $12
</P>
<P>
   Reservations: Not necessary.
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (904) 808-1999
</P>
<P>
   Ambiance: Clean. Homey kitchen, sunbathing area on the roof. No
TV. They rent bikes and surfboards.
</P>
<P>
   Key West
</P>
<P>
   Location: Within spitting distance of the southernmost point (if
you can spit about 100 yards). Old Town is within walking distance.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $17 for members, $20 for non-members
</P>
<P>
   Reservations: Recommended from December through March.
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (305) 296-5719.
</P>
<P>
   Ambiance: Busy. Picnic tables in the courtyard for socializing.
Dinner for $2. They also rent bikes and arrange snorkeling and
diving trips.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
