<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC WANTS RULING ON MATOCK INJURY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC expects to ask for a rules interpretation from
the Pacific-10 Conference on the play defensive tackle Marc Matock
broke his ankle against Arizona State.
</P>
<P>
   Matock suffered the injury after being hit from behind by
Arizona State center Grey Ruegamer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I felt it was an aggressive play. It was questionable,'' USC
assistant coach Ed Orgeron said. ``There's a lot of plays that are
questionable. We'll probably mention it because it was
questionable. We just want to find out the ruling on it. I wish it
wouldn't have happened.''
</P>
<P>
   Matock was clearly unhappy about the play after the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Ruegamer) came back and dove toward my ankle,'' Matock said.
</P>
<P>
   Every school submits a report to the Pac-10 after each game, and
game films are reviewed by Verle Sorgen, the conference's
coordinator of football officiating.
</P>
<P>
   Sorgen, who attended the game, said he expected to review the
reports and films later this week.
</P>
<P>
   Matock underwent surgery Sunday at USC University Hospital,
where he had a metal plate inserted in his ankle with six screws.
He is scheduled to be sidelined a minimum of two months and hopes
to return for a bowl game.
</P>
<P>
   With Matock out, Ennis Davis and Aaron Williams will start at
defensive tackle, with Ryan Nielsen switching from defensive end to
add depth.
</P>
<P>
   Cusano moving up? After another strong performance Saturday,
linebacker Mark Cusano could regain his starting job this week. For
the second straight game, Cusano had more tackles than starter Zeke
Moreno.
</P>
<P>
   Washington State game set: USC's game at Washington State on
Oct. 17 will begin at 7:15 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports
West. It's the second consecutive time the Trojans will be forced
to play in Pullman at night.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-05-98 2233EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
