<SLUG> BC-TIMES-APPOINTMENT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIMES APPOINTS CHIEF INFORMATION OFFICER 
</HEADLINE>
  (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Michael G. Williams has been appointed vice president
and chief information officer of The New York Times. His
appointment was announced Monday by Janet L. Robinson, the
newspaper's president and general manager.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, 42, had been vice president for information technology
and chief technology officer at the Seagram Co.'s Spirits and Wine
Group. He had been at Seagram since 1992, previously serving as
chief information officer of Seagram Asia-Pacific and in other
communications management positions. Before that Williams worked
for the Aetna Life and Casualty Co. and the Emery Air Freight Corp.
in telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
   Williams will be responsible for the development and maintenance
of business and publishing systems, the production of all Times
products printed by outside vendors, the newspaper's data center
and the administration of some business customer functions. He will
report to Richard H. Gilman, senior vice president for operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
